The Magpie impling is the fourth highest impling that can be caught in the Impetuous Impulses minigame, and are located throughout Puro-Puro and Gielinor. Players need at least 65 Hunter (or level 62-64 with a hunter potion) to capture this type of impling (75 barehanded). Capturing a Magpie impling will grant the player either 44 Hunter experience if caught in Puro-Puro, or 216 Hunter experience if caught outside of Puro-Puro, throughout Gielinor.

The Magpie impling is one of the most sought-after implings, alongside the Ninja impling and Dragon impling, due to the value of the loot from the Magpie impling being decently high.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening a magpie impling jar gives 16,850 worth of loot, on average. This means opening magpie impling jars marks an average profit of −7,462 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −373,083 to get a hard clue scroll from magpie impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.
